I saw this post by @danidlsa on Twitter:

When religious freedom becomes problematic…#TidyTuesday #rstats @R4DScommunity @tidypod

And decided to take a closer look at the exemption of vaccination (%) in New York schools. Most of the kids exempted for religious reasons are probably at private religious schools. To make sure of this, I downloaded data from the National Center for Education Statistics:

# Libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(maps)
library(ggrepel)

new.york.map <- map_data("county", region = "new york")

# Explore xrel in New York -----------------------------------------------------

school.orient <- readr::read_csv("pss1718_pu.csv") # This is a big data frame...the column I'm interested at is ORIENT

new.york <- new.york %>%
  mutate(name = tolower(name)) 


new.york.measles.rel <- school.orient %>%
  filter(PSTANSI == 36) %>% # 36 == New York
  mutate(name = tolower(PINST)) %>%
  select(c("LATITUDE18", "LONGITUDE18", "ORIENT", "PINST")) %>%
  right_join(new.york, by = c("LATITUDE18" = "lat", "LONGITUDE18" = "lng")) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = new.york.map, aes(long, lat, group = group), fill = "gray", colour = "black", size = 0.1) + 
  geom_point(aes(LONGITUDE18, LATITUDE18, colour = xrel), size = 0.5) + 
  geom_text_repel(aes(LONGITUDE18, LATITUDE18, colour = xrel, label = ifelse(xrel > 50, as.character(ORIENT), ""))) + 
  scale_colour_viridis_c(option = "plasma" ,name = "Students exempted from vaccination \nfor religious reasons (%)") + 
  facet_wrap(~type) + 
  theme_dark() + 
  theme(legend.position = "top")
new.york.measles.rel

3 - Amish; 5 - Baptist; 24 - Mennonite; 30 - Nonsectarian;

new.york.measles.med <- new.york %>%
  filter(lng < 0) %>%
  drop_na(xmed) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = new.york.map, aes(long, lat, group = group), fill = "gray", colour = "black", size = 0.1) + 
  geom_point(data = new.york, aes(lng, lat, colour = xmed), size = 0.5) + 
  scale_colour_viridis_c(option = "plasma", name = "Students exempted from vaccination \nfor medical reasons (%)") + 
  facet_wrap(~type) + 
  theme_dark() + 
  theme(legend.position = "top")
